726550f-a.text:
Farmers Boulevard, west side, at about One Hundred Twentieth Ave., showing another Charles De Bevoise house. Note that on the same side of the Boulevard were two homes situated closely together, one of which is the house in this view. Neither house was standing
in 1928.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726559f-a.text:
Farmers Boulevard, west side, opposite 120th Road, showing poosibly the Barr house, nonexistent in 1931.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726560f-a.text:
Farmers Boulevard, west side, opposite 120th Road (formerly Highland Ave.), showing in a set of two views what Jake Ryerson thinks is a Remsen house, according to the Collector.
1922.
View 2: September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster.
